# Claude in one page

## Which tool?

| You want to… | Use |
|---|---|
| Ask, learn, draft, brainstorm | **Chat** (claude.ai) |
| Repeated work with the same docs/instructions | Chat → **Project** |
| A doc/app/chart you can iterate & download | Chat → **Artifact** |
| Hand off a multi-step file task | **Cowork** (desktop app) |
| Write, fix, or understand code | **Claude Code** (terminal) |
| Slides, mockups, prototypes | **Claude Design** |
| Claude inside your email/calendar/files | **Connectors** |

## The prompt pattern

> **Role** · **Process** · **Standard** · **Guardrail**

*"You're the hiring manager for this role (role). Ask me six likely questions one at
a time (process). Give honest feedback using STAR (standard). Don't go easy on me
(guardrail)."*

Plus always: context, audience, format, length. Then **iterate** — the first answer
is draft one.

## The safety habits

- **Back up** before agents touch real files; scope access to one folder.
- **Read the diff / the proposed action** before approving.
- **Never paste:** passwords, keys, other people's personal data, unauthorized
  company data.
- **Verify before you submit** — especially citations and numbers.
- **The meeting test:** if you can't explain it without the chat open, you're not
  done yet.

## When stuck

Ask Claude itself → status.claude.com → support.claude.com → docs.claude.com
